NAME
    autologin - Configure automatic login
DESCRIPTION
    The AUTOLOGIN command is used to choose which user to select automatic login for. This is useful for single login systems, such as home users, as it means you don't have to type your username every time you log in.
SYNTAX
    autologin <username>
        Sets <username> as the autologin user.
    autologin --reset
        Disales autologin.
SEE ALSO
    user: Manages users
